After years of marinating anything I think needs to be grilled, I have discovered an amazing thing. You don't need to do it. A squeeze or two of lemon, salt and freshly ground pepper is all you need. The sauce is what takes the food to the next step. This is exactly what happened with this recipe. I had salmon filets. I had arugula. We were hungry but enjoying a wonderful Saturday night. So....lemon on the filets with salt and pepper. No sour cream...substituted creme fraiche and plain Stonyfield whole milk yogurt because although I love mayonnaise, homemade or Hellmanns I don't want to use it in a sauce on this... Fresh basil, more lemon..a bit of soy sauce..... Salmon comes off the grill, put on a bed of arugula..topped with the sauce and a bit of fresh ground pepper. What an amazing Saturday night...we'll share this with friends next time...

