This is a very, very good recipe, and I would rate it 3.5 forks if I only could. Be sure to use wild-caught sockeye salmon and marinate it in the oil-garlic mop prior to putting it on the grill. We also did the salmon on a cedar plank, but it took at least 20 to 25 minutes at 350 degrees on my gas grill. Make sure to use fresh horseradish in the sauce, and don't be afraid to double it. You could also double the amount of garlic in the mop, which is outstanding. Bottom line: We really enjoyed this recipe. But there is NO WAY it supplants Pan-Seared Tuna With Ginger-Shittake Cream Sauce as the greatest fish recipe on this site. I just can't agree with the husband of an earlier reviewer on that matter. This recipe is good. Very good. But it's not THAT good.

