Rating: 3
Very tasty and easy. I used 1/4 cup each mayo, plain yogurt and reduced fat sour cream for the sauce and substituted dill for the basil per others' recommendations. I added one Tablespoon of fresh lemon juice to the salmon marinade and marinated for one hour prior to baking (could not use my grill in the snow). Before baking at 425, I dried the salmon, spayed lightly with olive oil and rubbed it with a mix of chili powder, brown sugar, red and black pepper seasoning. I also finished the salmon by broiling it to crisp the top. Excellent!

